            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-1159] HttpClientUtils  - Helper methods to release resources of HttpClient / HttpResponse after use </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1159</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>Found myself writing this boiler plate code in various httpclient related projects , to release resources , and wanted to provide a simpler way to release resources similar to IOUtils.closeQuietly as opposed to maintaining the same in my code. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
New class: &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
o.a.http.client.utils.HttpClientUtils added: &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;pre&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public static void closeQuietly(final HttpResponse response); &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public static void closeQuietly(final HttpClient httpClient); &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/pre&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
with 2 methods ( as above ) in the same, to help release resources: &lt;br/&gt;
</description>
